Actor Uche Maduagwu has registered offered support for Mercy Aigbe’s union with ‘D owner’, Kazim Adeoti. As social media users continue to enunciate their stance over Mercy’s unveiling of her new hubby, the controversial actor taking to his Instagram page has now thrown his weight behind their union. While Maduagwu congratulated his colleague on her union with her new boo, he urged her to ignore naysayers who he noted are unstable like NEPA light. According to him, Aigbe should continue to pursue happiness which he described as the principal thing in life adding her union will not be separated by Fulani herdsmen or women that are excessively endowed because she’s been joined to her boo by the Almighty Allah.   Obi Cubana to Phyno: you look like Jesus     Sammie Okposo told me to get rid of pregnancy- African Doll     American mistress opens up on affair with Sammie Okposo   - Advertisement - “Congrats Mercy Aigbe. What Almighty Allah has joined together, no Fulani herdsmen or Ikebe FC ambassadors fit separate,” he wrote. “If dem fit critcise Pope, why dem no go criticise you? Se ogun laye ni? (Is life a war?)” He added: “Dear Mercy, happiness is the principal thing in life, and if God takes you from the VALLEY to the Mountain top to find am, my sister hold am tight because God-fearing husband material scarce for Naija. “You are not just a colleague but a good friend, the same people wey criticize Regina Daniel for marrying Ned no be dem dey congratulate am now?” “They are like NEPA light, so unstable yet criticise others, it is so worrisome that 90% of dem Na ladies when exactly are women going to start supporting women for Naija Ni Tori Olorun? (for God’s sake)”